Damage, fire & theft cover.$value: If you have an accident while driving, we’ll pay to fix the damage so you can get back on the road. And if your car is stolen, or it’s damaged by theft or fire, we’ll also repair or replace your car

Other people's car & property cover.$value: If you have an accident while driving and damage someone else’s car (or their property), we’ll pay to cover the car repair costs and fix the property damage.

Personal accident cover.$value: We hope you’ll never need it, but we give £5,000 of cover if you (or anyone else in the car) are accidentally killed, or suffer from a serious injury within 3 months of an incident. Under this cover, a serious injury would be: Permanent loss of sight

Courtesy car.$value: No wheels? No problem! 🚗 You’ll get a 3-door courtesy car on us when you make a valid claim. You’ll have it for as long as your car is being repaired after an accident, when you use our recommended repairers. Quick heads up - you won’t receive one if your car has been stolen or written off. If this is something you need, check out our courtesy car upgrade cover

Driving other cars cover.$value: You can drive another person’s car if it’s insured, you don’t own it, and you have the owner’s permission to drive it. 🙌 Quick heads up - if there was an accident, we’ll only pay for injury to others, or damage to other cars or property, not for the car you’re driving

Uninsured driver promise.$value: If an uninsured driver damages your car, you won’t pay an excess and you won’t lose your No Claims Discount (NCD), as long as the incident wasn’t your fault, and you can give us details of the car 😇

Windscreen cover.$value: Whether it’s a small chip, or a smashed windscreen, we’ve got you covered. We’ll repair or replace your glass windscreen or windows (but not your sunroof though, sorry!) And if your paintwork is scratched due to smashed glass, we’ll fix that as well 🩹

Key cover.$value: Phone? Check! Keys? Oh… Don't worry - you'll get up to £500 of cover if your keys are lost, damaged or stolen 🔑

Misfuelling cover.$value: Distracted by what you’re having for tea and put the wrong fuel in your car? 🍕We've got you – we'll drain, then flush the tank and put new fuel in for yo

Add-on-Legal.$value: If you need to claim for uninsured losses (like missed earnings) after an accident that wasn't your fault, we'll be there for you with up to £100,000 of legal fees cover.

Add-on-Breakdown.$value: Don't let a breakdown ruin your day. We've got your back with four different levels of breakdown cover.

Add-on-Protected NCD.$value: Is your NCD stacked high? Keep it when you protect it with us - even if you're the one who makes a mistake.

Add-on-Courtesy car upgrade.$value: Get a car that's a little more you - whether yours is a bit bling or a bit bland, we'll give you a car that's similar to yours when you claim.

What you'll pay if you make a claim-subc.$value: Excess is the amount you pay when you claim. Remember - when you claim you'll need to pay this, so only choose what you'd be happy to pay. Make sure you don't choose an excess that’s more than the value of your car, otherwise your policy may not pay out if your car is written off as a result of a claim.

UK resident - subcopy.$value: If you live less than nine months per year in the UK, you should choose Not a UK resident.

UK resident (additional driver)- subcopy.$value: If they live less than nine months per year in the UK, you should choose Not a UK resident.

Important info-Right to cancel-body.$value: If you cancel before your policy starts we will refund your premium in full.  You have 14 days from the start date of the policy when you can cancel this policy for no fee. If you cancel after 14 days from the start date, there's a £52.50 administration fee.  When you cancel your policy, provided you haven't made a claim or had an accident which may lead to a claim, we'll keep your premium for the time you've been covered with us and refund the rest to you. If there's a claim on the policy, you'll need to pay the full premium for the year.
